Chapter Eighteen
2004

The resort was the same tacky, whitewashed Mission Revival style as
their school, only with more glass. Nick supposed this was supposed to
capitalize on the beachfront aesthetics that came from the ocean and the
incredibly blue skies but because it was the obvious choice, it disappointed
him.
He liked their rooms better, which were icy and modern. Shag rugs in
cool tones, modern furniture with chrome, white couches. Jay raced around,
