Do you really hate me, Jay?
Jay sat in the cabana lounge, clutching her purse. She was wearing one
of the sundresses that she'd bought with Nick, which she now regretted
bringing. She didn't like any of the clothes she had taken with her—
expensive, revealing, not her style at all. What she really wanted was jeans
